==English==

===Etymology===
The phrase, one of the most famous rallying cries of [[communism]], comes from [[w:Karl Marx|Karl Marx]] and [[w:Friedrich Engels|Friedrich Engels's]] ''[[w:The Communist Manifesto|The Communist Manifesto]]''. A variation ("Workers of all lands, unite!") is inscribed on [[:File:KarlMarx_Tomb.JPG|Marx's tombstone]]. The actual translation is more normally given as "Working men", or "[[proletarian|Proletarian]]s of all countries, unite!" (''Proletarier aller Länder, vereinigt euch!'').

===Phrase===
{{wikipedia|Workers of the world, unite!}}
{{infl|en|phrase|head=[[worker]]s [[of]] [[the]] [[world]], [[unite]]}}!

# [[laborer|Laborer]]s are encouraged to [[unionize]] or otherwise engage in [[collective]] action in order to use the strength of their numbers to obtain better conditions.

